text: Enchanted Golden Boots with Soul Speed[J]
Enchanted Golden Boots with Soul Speed[J]
Added redstone dust to dungeon chests, sometime between its introduction in Alpha v1.0.1 and 1.0.4.
Added the newly introduced 13 and cat music discs to dungeon chests.
Cocoa beans could be found in dungeon chests.
Added abandoned mineshafts with their chests.
Added strongholds with library and storeroom chests.
Strongholds now also have chests in corridor altars.
Village blacksmith houses now generate with chests.
Added jungle and desert temples with their chests.
Enchanted books added to dungeon, temple, mineshaft and stronghold chests.
Name tags are added to dungeon chests.
Cocoa beans are removed from dungeon chests.
Chests now generate in Nether fortresses.

Recently introduced, horse armor can now be found in jungle & desert temple, dungeon, Nether fortress, stronghold altar and village chests; iron horse armor can additionally be found in mineshaft chests.
Acacia wood can now be found in bonus chests.
Obsidian can now be found in nether fortress chests.
Music discs are made more rare in dungeon chests.
Added end cities with their chests.
Reduced nether fortress loot from 2–5 stacks to 2–4.
Increased stronghold library loot from 1–4 stacks to 2–10.
Changed enchanted books rate in stronghold libraries, from groups of 1–5 with weight 2, to single books with weight 10.
Wood in bonus chests can now be of any type, rather than just acacia and oak.
Planks in bonus chests can now be of any type, rather than just oak.
Changed golden apples in igloo chests to a 100% chance.
Chests in mineshafts, desert pyramids, simple dungeons and bonus chests pull loot from multiple pools, and their items are significantly rebalanced.
Saddle and iron horse armor are removed from mineshaft chests; name tag, torch, golden apple, enchanted golden apple, powered rail, detector rail, and activator rail are added.
Spider eye, gunpowder, string, sand, golden apple, and enchanted golden apple are added to desert chests.
Salmon is added to bonus chests. This chest now always contains one axe, one pickaxe, some food, and some wood items. Sticks and planks are made more plentiful.
Bone, rotten flesh, gold ingot, coal, enchanted golden apple, melon, pumpkin and beetroot seeds are added to simple dungeon chests.
Added woodland mansions with their chests.
Added underwater ruins with their chests.
Added buried treasure with their chests.
Added bamboo and suspicious stew to shipwreck chests. (Verify)
Added pillager outposts with their chests.
Added bastion remnants and ruined portals with their chests.
Removed netherite gear, made ancient debris and netherite scrap less common, and added enchanted crossbows to bastion remnant chests.
Weight of golden apples in ruined portal chests decreased from 40 to 15.
Moss blocks can be found in supply chests.

texts.text: This table summarizes the average quantity of each item that can be found in a naturally-generated chest, depending on its location.
In Java Edition, values represent the number of items expected per chest, averaged over a large number of chests.
In Java Edition 1.19[upcoming], values represent the number of items expected per chest, averaged over a large number of chests.
In Bedrock Edition, values represent the number of items expected per chest, averaged over a large number of chests.
In Bedrock Edition 1.18.30 (Vanilla Experiments)[upcoming], values represent the number of items expected per chest, averaged over a large number of chests.

The meaning of these naturally generated chests is that the loot type has not yet been determined. The contents generate when a player interacts with the chest by opening it, placing a hopper under it, inserting an item using a hopper, or destroying it.
There are different kinds of loot tables, for example a desert temple or a stronghold.

In Java Edition 1.12 and below, the /setblock command can be used to place a chest. The command /setblock ~ ~ ~ minecraft:chest 2 replace {LootTable:"chests/simple_dungeon"} sets the chest to a dungeon chest. For a minecart chest, use /summon chest_minecart ~ ~ ~ {LootTable:"chests/simple_dungeon"} instead.
In Java Edition 1.13 and above, the syntax has changed to e.g. /setblock ~ ~ ~ chest{LootTable:"chests/simple_dungeon"} replace

Note that this artificial chest is random every time you place one, no matter the location. That is a difference between normal natural chests and artificial loot tables chests. You can set the seed of the loot table using LootTableSeed, by default it is the world seed.
